<sect2 id="script-fu-circuit">
  <title>Line Nova</title>

  <indexterm>
    <primary>Filters</primary>
    <secondary>Render</secondary>
    <tertiary>Line Nova</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Line Nova</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect3>
    <title>Overview</title>
    <figure>
      <title>Example of Line Nova</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata format="JPG"
            fileref="images/filters/examples/render-taj-line-nova.jpg"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>
          <para>Filter <quote>Line Nova</quote> applied</para>
        </caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>
      <guimenuitem>Line Nova</guimenuitem> command is a script which fills
      a layer with rays emanating outward from its center using the FG color.
      All lines radiates from the center of the layer.  Rendered lines are
      cropped to be fit inside of the image.
    </para>
    <tip>
      <para>
        This filter does not have any option which allow you to set the center
        point of lines.  If you need adjust the center of lines, create another
        transparent image and apply this filter on it, then add it on your
        image.  When creating the new transparent image, set size larger than
        your image so that its lines would not break inside of your image.
      </para>
    </tip>
  </sect3>

  <sect3>
    <title>Options</title>
    <figure>
      <title><quote>Line Nova</quote> filter options</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata format="PNG"
            fileref="images/filters/render/line-nova.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>
      1
    </para>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Number of lines</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            By using this slider you can set the number of lines between 40
            to 1000. The default is 200.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Sharpness (degrees)</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            0.0-10.0 1.0
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Offset radius</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            0-2000 100
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Randomness</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            1-2000 30
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
